parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut down or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Dashboard lights and audio system shut off randomly
loss of power when shutting off the truck
service messages for power steering
StabiliTrak
and trailering appear on the DIC.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Service trailer brake system warning message appears on the instrument panel
audible warning chime sounds
trailer brake control default message displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overly bright display can impair night vision, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brightness level for the center console display cannot be dimmed
banner displayed along the top of the screen is too bright at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine block heater issue can cause fires, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine block heater cord rubs against sharp edges
exposing bare wire
short circuits
and fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's intermittent starting issue can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle intermittently will not start
DIC displays service messages for power steering
StabiliTrak
and trailering.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Motive Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of motive power can cause accidents, especially if the vehicle stalls while driving at high speeds. This can lead to a loss of control, increasing the risk of crashes and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
loses motive power
and may experience difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An abnormal engine noise can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, which if left unchecked, can lead to engine failure, causing a loss of motive power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle produces an abnormal sound while driving at various speeds or while idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repairs can lead to a prolonged exposure to potential safety risks, increasing the likelihood of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle is subject to a recall
but the necessary parts are not available
and the manufacturer is unable to provide a timeline for the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning torque converter can cause the vehicle to shudder or lurch, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences frequent shuddering or lurching at specific acceleration speeds
such as 30 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy upon impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Passenger Seat Belt Warning System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of a passenger seat belt warning system can lead to occupants not wearing their seatbelts, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: No passenger seat belt warning audio or visual
no sensor to detect occupancy
no dash indicator showing passenger seat belt status.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate passenger airbag system can lead to ineffective protection in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Passenger airbag system is active full-time but only marginally effective if the passenger fails to secure their seatbelt
no dash indicator showing passenger seat belt status.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Equipment (NHTSA Campaign Number: 21V496000)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair for equipment can lead to potential safety hazards and inconvenience to vehicle owners, as they are left waiting for the necessary parts to become available.
symptoms: Notification of recall received
but parts are not available for repair
dealer confirms parts are not available
manufacturer is aware of the issue
and repair is delayed.
